        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 8 at 5:21AM CST by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>Areas of fog, some locally dense, have developed across portions
of Deep South Texas this morning. Expect visibilities generally 3
miles or less with a few locations seeing visibilities 1/2 mile
or less at times.

Use caution if traveling as visibility may change rapidly
in a short amount of time. Use low beam headlights and leave
extra distance between your vehicle and others on the road.
</description>
